text: It's not really a computer. The monitor in your ship is nothing more than a journal. When your character learns something new while exploring they write it into their ships log. The reason the ships logs don't reset after each loop is because it's somehow linked to the memory statue (or at least that is what is implied by the blue lights leading into it). I don't think that is ever really explained, I believe the ships log is more of just a visual representation of the knowledge your character currently has
author: @rcm616-j5t

text: ¬†@rcm616-j5t¬† The computer has a image of the broken orbital probe cannon. The player character may be writing information into the computer, but they don't appear to be drawing new images. author: @TonkarzOfSolSystem

text: ¬†@TonkarzOfSolSystem¬† ohh okay, it's because the very first thing you see upon opening your eyes at the start of each loop is the orbital probe cannon firing and falling apart. Looking forwards to seeing you in Shion's live! :_EbiPen:Take care now sharky~ gotta protect the voicebox.
